# Release Artifacts Organization

When creating a new release, follow this structure and process.

## Folder Structure

```
releases/
  v{VERSION}/
    chrome/
      offlyn-apply-chrome-v{VERSION}.zip
    firefox/
      offlyn-apply-firefox-v{VERSION}.zip
    native-helpers/
      offlyn-helper-signed.pkg        (macOS)
      offlyn-windows-installer.bat    (Windows)
  archive/
    (older versions moved here)
```

## Release Process

### 1. Version Bump
Update version in ALL of these files:
- `apps/extension-chrome/package.json`
- `apps/extension-firefox/package.json`
- `apps/extension-chrome/public/manifest.json`
- `apps/extension-firefox/public/manifest.json`

### 2. Build Extensions
```bash
cd apps/extension-chrome && npm run build
cd apps/extension-firefox && npm run build
```

### 3. Create Release Artifacts
```bash
# Create folder structure
mkdir -p releases/v{VERSION}/chrome releases/v{VERSION}/firefox releases/v{VERSION}/native-helpers

# Create Chrome zip
cd apps/extension-chrome/dist && zip -r ../../../releases/v{VERSION}/chrome/offlyn-apply-chrome-v{VERSION}.zip .

# Create Firefox zip
cd apps/extension-firefox/dist && zip -r ../../../releases/v{VERSION}/firefox/offlyn-apply-firefox-v{VERSION}.zip .

# Copy native helpers (if updated)
cp scripts/native-host/offlyn-helper-signed.pkg releases/v{VERSION}/native-helpers/
cp scripts/offlyn-windows-installer.bat releases/v{VERSION}/native-helpers/
```

### 4. Archive Previous Version
Move previous version's artifacts to `releases/archive/` before creating new release.

## Naming Convention

- Chrome: `offlyn-apply-chrome-v{VERSION}.zip`
- Firefox: `offlyn-apply-firefox-v{VERSION}.zip`
- macOS Helper: `offlyn-helper-signed.pkg`
- Windows Helper: `offlyn-windows-installer.bat`

## Important Notes

- The `releases/` folder is in `.gitignore` - artifacts are not committed to git
- Always bump version in BOTH package.json AND manifest.json files
- Keep archive folder for rollback capability
- Native helpers only need updating if the helper scripts changed
